                        <extent>117 folios 
									
								</extent>
                        <foliation>Original Hebrew foliation added by a later hand, only partly visible. </foliation>
                        <collation>
                           <p>
									17 quires extant, of 6 to 7 leaves each.
									Imperfect at the beginning and at the end.  
								</p>
                        </collation>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <p>Columns: 2;
                                                  ruled lines: 29;
                                                  written lines: 29; Visible bifolio ruling with hard point. Zechariah opens a new column, and Jeremiah, Obadiah and Nahum commence a new leaf. The chapters have been numbered with Hebrew letters by a later hand, but not throughout the whole  manuscript.Masorah magna occupies two lines in the upper and three in the lower margin of each page. The titles of the books are written at the top of the recto of each folio. A number of masoretic notes appear at the beginning of Jeremiah, 25r-25v. </p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
